    <string name="kosail">Made by kosail</string>

    <string name="about_this_app">Details about this app</string>
    <string name="tribute_zero">
        Aria is a handcrafted tribute to Blanket, a Linux ambient sounds app originally created by Rafael Mardojai as part of the GNOME Circle.
    </string>
    <string name="tribute_one">
        Though beautiful, it was only for Linux. I rebuilt it from scratch for many other devices because I wanted that my mom had better sleep without spending too much mobile data on YouTube videos.
    </string>

    <string name="tribute_two">
        This project is a complete rewrite designed to run across multiple platforms, including Android, Desktop, and Linux environments.
        Like the original, Aria has no accounts, no ads, and no unnecessary complexity. Just ambient soundscapes to help you focus or rest.
    </string>
    <string name="tribute_three">
        Aria is free and open-source software. Its source code is publicly available, and anyone can build and distribute it under the terms of the GPLv3 license.
    </string>
    <string name="tribute_four">
        The Android version on the Play Store is a paid distribution. Purchasing it supports ongoing development, maintenance, and future improvements.
        You are always free to obtain, modify, and share the app independently under the same license.
    </string>

    <string name="donations_text">
        If you enjoy Aria and find it useful, you can support its development with a voluntary donation.

        Your support helps keep the project free, open-source, and actively maintained.
    </string>
